  "prompt": "Is there something that Sachin Tendulkar has not done in cricket?",
  "response": "Sachin Tendulkar, often hailed as one of the greatest cricketers of all time, has achieved an extraordinary amount in his illustrious career. However, there are a few notable things he has not accomplished in cricket:\n\n1. **Win a World Cup as Captain**: Sachin Tendulkar was part of the Indian team that won the 2011 ICC Cricket World Cup, but he was not the captain. He did captain India in the 1996 World Cup, but the team did not win the tournament.\n\n2. **Score a Triple Century in Test Cricket**: Despite being the highest run-scorer in Test cricket, Sachin's highest score in Tests is 248 not out. He never reached the 300-run mark, a milestone achieved by several other batsmen.\n\n3. **Score a Double Century in ODIs Before 2010**: Although Sachin became the first player to score a double century in ODIs in 2010 (200* against South Africa), he did not achieve this milestone earlier in his career.\n\n4. **Win an ICC T20 World Cup**: Sachin Tendulkar did not play in the inaugural ICC T20 World Cup in 2007, which India won. T20 cricket became more prominent towards the end of his career, and he didn't participate in the T20 World Cup tournaments.\n\n5. **Play County Cricket for an Extended Period**: While Sachin has had brief stints in county cricket, he never had a prolonged career in the English County Championship, unlike some of his contemporaries.\n\n6. **Take a Five-Wicket Haul in International Cricket**: Sachin was a handy occasional bowler with 200+ international wickets, but he never took a five-wicket haul in any format of international cricket.\n\nThese are minor exclusions in an otherwise flawless career. Tendulkar's legacy is defined by his consistency, longevity, and numerous records, making him a cricketing legend.",
